00:19:57.070 --> 00:19:58.540
&gt;&gt; Frederic Rzewski: In fact
maybe somebody in the audience --

00:19:58.540 --> 00:20:02.570
I heard already some
-- just heard protest.

00:20:02.570 --> 00:20:07.040
Can somebody tell us what
this word actually means?

00:20:07.040 --> 00:20:11.550
No hu? Well, I often, you know,
talk to my students about this.

00:20:11.550 --> 00:20:14.710
Well, I lived in Italy
for a long time.

00:20:14.710 --> 00:20:18.010
So, the word is conservatorio.

00:20:18.010 --> 00:20:20.560
Now, what is a conservatorio?

00:20:20.560 --> 00:20:29.540
It is an orphanage because in the
middle ages the church received --

00:20:29.540 --> 00:20:34.330
you can still see them in certain
places, in Padua for example,

00:20:34.330 --> 00:20:39.940
in front of the Cathedral of Saint
Anthony there is a curious rotund

00:20:39.940 --> 00:20:44.410
structure, which has a little
door on it and there's a kind

00:20:44.410 --> 00:20:47.420
of lazy Susan inside the door.

00:20:47.420 --> 00:20:51.360 position:56%
Now the whole point of that is that
behind the door on the other side --

00:20:51.360 --> 00:20:57.410
behind it on the other side there's
a similar door with a nun waiting

00:20:57.410 --> 00:21:04.260
and what you do is if you have a
child which you really can't afford

00:21:04.260 --> 00:21:09.340
to bring up, instead of throwing
it in the river you take it

00:21:09.340 --> 00:21:11.900
to the church, put it in there,

00:21:11.900 --> 00:21:16.550
and on the other side the nun
takes the baby and that's it.

00:21:16.550 --> 00:21:19.260
You never make eye
contact or anything.

00:21:19.260 --> 00:21:26.040
And so many children were saved
or conservati in this way.

00:21:26.040 --> 00:21:28.120
So, the place where --

00:21:28.120 --> 00:21:32.210
which receives these children
there is a conservatori,

00:21:32.210 --> 00:21:34.420
or place where they are saved.

00:21:34.420 --> 00:21:41.840 position:56%
And of course the church brings them
up and teaches them to do things

00:21:41.840 --> 00:21:47.050
like decorating the church,
singing in the choir.

00:21:47.050 --> 00:21:51.510
So, many of the famous
painters of the renaissance

00:21:51.510 --> 00:21:57.870
and musicians were
[laughs] saved in this way.

00:21:57.870 --> 00:22:02.080 position:56%
And only in the eighteenth century
did Caro Bini [phonetic spelling] go

00:22:02.080 --> 00:22:06.550
to Paris and start the
first conservatoire,

00:22:06.550 --> 00:22:11.560
which then was -- became
a music school.

00:22:11.560 --> 00:22:13.650
But that's not what the word means.

00:22:13.650 --> 00:22:15.570
&gt;&gt; David Plylar: I wasn't really
